Sentencas: The pure cubic perovskite structure of BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-delta could be maintained when the Ni-doping concentration is ranged from 15 to 20%.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The characteristics of BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-delta (x = 0.15, 0.2, BZFN) cubic perovskite oxides are investigated systematically to develop a low-cost and cobalt-free cathode for protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFCs).
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: There is a good chemical compatibility between BZFN and BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY) materials.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The BaZr0.1Fe0.75Ni0.15O3-delta (BZFN15) material exhibits more rich oxygen vacancies, higher electrical conductivity and surface exchange coefficients, and better oxygen adsorption ability than BaZr0.1Fe0.7Ni0.2O3-delta (BZFN20).
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The symmetrical cell with BZFN15-BZCY composite cathode shows lower polarization resistance than that with BZFN20-BZCY composite cathode, e. g. 0.36 vs 0.41 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The distribution of relaxation times (DRT) analysis of the cathode process reveals that the main rate-limiting step is oxygen adsorption and dissociation.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes

Sentencas: The anode-supported single cell with the BZFN15-BZCY cathode displays high power density of 583 mW cm(-2) and low polarization resistance of 0.087 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, demonstrating the potential of the BZFN15 oxide as PCFC cathode.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Fe0.9-xNixO3-δ cubic perovskite oxides for protonic ceramic fuel cell cathodes
